---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const siblingServices = [
  { name: "Root Canal Treatment", href: "/services/endodontics/root-canal" },
  { name: "Traumatic Dental Injuries", href: "/services/endodontics/traumatic-injuries" },
  { name: "Cracked Tooth", href: "/services/endodontics/cracked-tooth" },
  { name: "Internal Bleaching", href: "/services/endodontics/internal-bleaching", current: true },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Internal Bleaching | Endodontic Care | Wildwood Dental Clinic Saskatoon"
  description="Internal tooth bleaching at Wildwood Dental Clinic in Saskatoon, a procedure to lighten a tooth that has darkened after root canal treatment."
>

  <!-- ============================================================
       HERO
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] relative overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Right-side image panel, desktop only -->
    <div class="hidden lg:block absolute right-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-[42%] pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true">
      <img
        src="/images/services/endodontics-procedure.jpg"
        alt=""
        width="800"
        height="600"
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 w-2/3" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--color-brand-primary), transparent);"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container-wide relative py-16 lg:py-24 lg:max-w-[64%]">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] mb-5" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <a href="/services" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Services</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <a href="/services/endodontics" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Endodontic Services</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span class="text-white">Internal Bleaching</span>
      </nav>
      <p class="eyebrow text-[var(--color-brand-accent-soft)]">Endodontic Care</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-5xl)] leading-tight text-white max-w-2xl">
        Internal Bleaching
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
        Internal bleaching is a procedure used to address discolouration in a tooth that has had root canal treatment. Rather than working on the tooth's outer surface, a bleaching agent is placed inside the tooth to address the source of the colour change from within.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       MAIN CONTENT + SIDEBAR
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section-y bg-white">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_300px] gap-12">

        <!-- LEFT: Main content -->
        <div class="space-y-10">

          <!-- What it is -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              What is internal bleaching?
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Internal bleaching is a procedure performed on teeth that have already undergone root canal treatment and have subsequently darkened. Unlike conventional tooth whitening, which is applied to the outside surfaces of the teeth, internal bleaching involves placing a bleaching agent inside the pulp chamber of the tooth to address intrinsic discolouration that originates from within the tooth structure.
              </p>
              <p>
                The procedure makes use of the access opening that was created during the original root canal treatment, so no additional drilling into the tooth structure is typically required.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Image break -->
          <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
            <img
              src="/images/sourced/service-endodontics-tmd-treatment.jpg"
              alt="Endodontic and TMD treatment procedure"
              width="800"
              height="450"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
              class="w-full h-56 sm:h-72 object-cover"
            />
          </div>


          <!-- Why a tooth darkens -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              Why does a tooth darken after root canal treatment?
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Teeth that have had root canal treatment may darken over time for several reasons. Remnants of pulp tissue left in the pulp chamber can break down and release pigment compounds into the surrounding dentine. Blood breakdown products from the initial injury or treatment can also stain the tooth structure from within. In some cases, certain dental materials used during root canal treatment can contribute to discolouration over time.
              </p>
              <p>
                This type of discolouration originates inside the tooth, which is why conventional external whitening typically has little effect on these teeth, the colour change is coming from within the dentine and cannot be adequately reached from the outside.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- The procedure -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              How the procedure works
            </h2>
            <ol class="space-y-5">
              {[
                ["Access and preparation", "The access opening from the original root canal is reopened. A barrier material is placed over the root canal filling to protect the root from the bleaching agent."],
                ["Placement of bleaching agent", "A bleaching agent is sealed inside the pulp chamber and the tooth is temporarily sealed with a provisional restoration."],
                ["Review and repeat if needed", "At a follow-up appointment, we assess the degree of colour change. The process may be repeated over several visits, depending on the extent of the discolouration and the response of the tooth."],
                ["Final restoration", "Once a satisfactory colour change has been achieved, the bleaching agent is removed and the tooth is permanently sealed, typically with composite resin."],
              ].map(([title, text], i) => (
                <li class="flex gap-4">
                  <span class="shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] text-white text-sm font-semibold flex items-center justify-center mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true">{i + 1}</span>
                  <div>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)]">{title}</p>
                    <p class="mt-1 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">{text}</p>
                  </div>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ol>
          </div>

          <!-- Results -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              What to expect regarding results
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Internal bleaching can reduce intrinsic discolouration to varying degrees. The extent of colour change depends on the nature and severity of the discolouration, how long the tooth has been darkened, and individual tooth characteristics. Some teeth respond more readily than others.
              </p>
              <p>
                In cases where bleaching achieves only partial improvement, or where the tooth does not respond adequately to bleaching, alternative approaches, such as composite bonding or a veneer, can be used to address the remaining colour difference from the outside.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Who is a candidate -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-cool)] rounded-2xl p-7 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-2xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] leading-tight">
              Who is a candidate?
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Internal bleaching is appropriate for patients who have a tooth that has darkened following root canal treatment, where the tooth is otherwise structurally sound and the root canal is intact and well-sealed. It is not suitable for teeth with structural compromise, active infection, or inadequate root canal treatment.
              </p>
              <p>
                A clinical assessment and x-rays are required to confirm suitability before proceeding. If internal bleaching is not appropriate in your case, we will discuss the alternatives available to you.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Alternatives -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              If internal bleaching is not sufficient
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                If internal bleaching does not achieve adequate colour change, or is not suitable in a particular case, there are other options that may be considered:
              </p>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-3">
                {[
                  "Composite bonding applied to the front surface of the tooth to mask residual discolouration",
                  "A porcelain veneer, which covers the visible surface of the tooth with a thin layer of ceramic",
                ].map(item => (
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <svg class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="5 12 10 17 19 7"/></svg>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">{item}</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-3">
                The most appropriate option depends on the degree of discolouration, the overall condition of the tooth, and the patient's preferences. We discuss all available options at the consultation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Specialty disclaimer -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-alt)] rounded-2xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-accent)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-base text-[var(--color-brand-primary)]">About our endodontic services</h3>
                <p class="mt-1.5 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
                  Endodontic services at Wildwood Dental Clinic are provided by our general dentist team. Our dentists are not licensed specialists in endodontics.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- RIGHT: Sidebar -->
        <aside class="space-y-6">

          <!-- Book CTA card -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] rounded-2xl p-6 text-white">
            <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-white">Ready to Book?</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] leading-relaxed">Call us or book your appointment online.</p>
            <a href="/book" class="mt-4 btn btn-primary w-full block text-center">Request Appointment</a>
            <a href="tel:+13063747272" class="mt-2 block text-center text-sm text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] hover:text-white transition-colors">306.374.7272</a>
          </div>

          <!-- Sibling services card -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-cool)] rounded-2xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <h3 class="font-body text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">Endodontic Services</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              {siblingServices.map(svc => (
                <li>
                  {svc.current ? (
                    <span class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]">
                      <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-accent)] shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                      {svc.name}
                    </span>
                  ) : (
                    <a href={svc.href} class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent)] transition-colors">
                      <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-border-soft)] shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                      {svc.name}
                    </a>
                  )}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>

        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       CTA BAND
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] py-16 text-center overflow-hidden relative">
    <svg class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full pointer-events-none" viewBox="0 0 1440 160" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
      <path d="M0 60 C 240 20, 480 100, 720 60 C 960 20, 1200 100, 1440 60 L1440 160 L0 160 Z" fill="rgba(255,255,255,0.03)"/>
    </svg>
    <div class="relative container-wide">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-4xl)] text-white leading-tight">Have questions about internal bleaching?</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto">Call <a href="tel:+13063747272" class="text-white font-semibold hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent-soft)] transition-colors">306.374.7272</a> or book a consultation.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/book" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Request an Appointment</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-lg border border-white/30 text-white hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">Contact Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
